Honestly, this place is OKAY. It's not great. It's not bad either. They have cheap prices, so you get what you pay for. The customer service here is hectic, but it's not like you're paying for a sit in restaurant. However, I had to dock one point for cleanliness. Phew, this place does not look like it would pass a DOH inspection. The trays they give food are aren't always clean. And for some reason, there's a layer of perpetual grime on the floor that you can not only see, but is off-putting. Another point was docked for the quality of the food. Even for the prices, it really did feel like I was eating cardboard instead of meat. The sauces were the only real flavor. All in all, this place is good if you need a quick bite for cheap; but other than that avoid avoid avoid! They don't have seating capable of large groups either. Wait time is short though.

I ordered from them delivery yesterday. I ordered the total 0f 21$, and the amount of food I got was huge! So for the prices they definitely have 5 stars from me. Now for the food: First, the soft tacos is are wrapped with tortilla which is way too thick for my taste. I t is taking over the taste of the tacos. And I think that you should never deliver tacos with no slices of Lemon on the side, even if the customer did not specifically asked for it. The hard tacos were fine. I had the grilled chicken tacos. The chicken of the “Grilled chicken and rise” is very good, but a little dry for my taste. The salad that also come in the box was very fresh, and I know it was made just before they sent the delivery. There is nothing that I dislike more than a salad which was cut long time ago, I just feel the difference immediately. The Cheese Quesadilla was very good. And it was a nice finale for a huge dinner ;)  I will order from them again.
